<paragraph id="8BC336F6FFA04401D3EBFBEBFE00FBB1" blockId="2.[151,476,1050,1077]" box="[151,476,1050,1077]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">
<heading id="D08B819AFFA04401D3EBFBEBFE00FBB1" bold="true" box="[151,476,1050,1077]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D3EBFBEBFE00FBB1" bold="true" box="[151,476,1050,1077]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D3EBFBEBFEFFFBB1" baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[151,291,1050,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D3EBFBEBFEFFFBB1" bold="true" box="[151,291,1050,1077]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D22FFBEBFE00FBB1" authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[339,476,1050,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D22FFBEBFE00FBB1" bold="true" box="[339,476,1050,1077]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C366657DFFA04401D3EBFB92FD16F939" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC336F6FFA04401D3EBFB92FCF8FAD1" blockId="2.[151,1437,1123,1725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">
While describing 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D221FB92FD54FBFA" authority=", Pascoe (1866)" authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[349,648,1123,1150]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D221FB92FE07FBF9" box="[349,475,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B07FFA04401D295FB92FD54FBFA" author="Pascoe, F. P." box="[489,648,1123,1150]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="225 - 336" refId="ref4447" refString="Pascoe, F. P. (1866) Longicornia Malayana; or, a Descriptive Catalogue of the Species of the three Longicorn Families Lamiidae, Cerambycidae and Prionidae collected by Mr. A. R. Wallace in the Malay Archipelago. (Part III). The Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 3 (3) 3, 225 - 336, pls X-XV." type="journal article" year="1866">Pascoe (1866)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
did not take into account 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D0DBFB92FBFFFBF9" baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[935,1059,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D0DBFB92FBFFFBF9" box="[935,1059,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but considered both genera in the key to the Malayan 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D208FB76FD51FB26" authority="(Pascoe, 1866)" baseAuthorityName="Pascoe" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[372,653,1159,1186]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lamiinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
Lamiinae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B07FFA04401D290FB76FD59FB26" author="Pascoe, F. P." box="[492,645,1159,1186]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="225 - 336" refId="ref4447" refString="Pascoe, F. P. (1866) Longicornia Malayana; or, a Descriptive Catalogue of the Species of the three Longicorn Families Lamiidae, Cerambycidae and Prionidae collected by Mr. A. R. Wallace in the Malay Archipelago. (Part III). The Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 3 (3) 3, 225 - 336, pls X-XV." type="journal article" year="1866">Pascoe, 1866</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D1EBFB76FCC9FB25" authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[663,789,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D1EBFB76FCC9FB25" box="[663,789,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was keyed differently due to the “elytra not toothed at the shoulders”, while the original description expressly stated the opposite (“ 
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D0ADFB5AFEDCFB6D" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Elytra sub-angustata, humeris in dentem productis</emphasis>
”). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B07FFA04401D259FB3EFE1DFB6E" author="Gahan, C. J." box="[293,449,1231,1258]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="109 - 121" refId="ref4312" refString="Gahan, C. J. (1906) On a Collection of Longicorn Coleoptera from Selangor and Perak. Journal of the Federated Malay States Museum, 1, 109 - 121, pl. VI. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938809460949" type="journal article" year="1906">Gahan (1906)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D130FB3EFD16FB6D" authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[588,714,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D130FB3EFD16FB6D" box="[588,714,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D0EBFB3EFBCFFB6D" baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[919,1043,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D0EBFB3EFBCFFB6D" box="[919,1043,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without providing any differential characters. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B07FFA04401D26BFB02FE18FA89" author="Ritsema, C." box="[279,452,1267,1293]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="191 - 192" refId="ref4614" refString="Ritsema, C. (1914) Note XX. A new Sumatran Longicorn Beetle. Notes from the Leyden Museum, 36 (3 - 4), 191 - 192." type="journal article" year="1914">Ritsema (1914)</bibRefCitation>
and Aurivillius (1922) considered these as separate genera, without stating any reasons. Finally, Breuning (1943) keyed both genera differently, due to the scape with closed (
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D722FAE6FB06FAB5" baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[1118,1242,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D722FAE6FB06FAB5" box="[1118,1242,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or open cicatrix (
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D3DDFACAFEC3FAD1" authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[161,287,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D3DDFACAFEC3FAD1" box="[161,287,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Actually, the cicatrix is open in both genera.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC336F6FFA04401D3BBFAAEFCD0F9A9" blockId="2.[151,1437,1123,1725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D3BBFAAEFE9FFAFD" baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[199,323,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D3BBFAAEFE9FFAFD" box="[199,323,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D206FAAEFE24FAFD" authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[378,504,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D206FAAEFE24FAFD" box="[378,504,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are closely related taxa, as supported by the facts that 
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B07FFA04401D720FAAEFACAFAFD" author="Breuning, S. von" box="[1116,1302,1375,1401]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="9 - 29" refId="ref4226" refString="Breuning, S. von (1982) Diagnoses preliminaires de nouveaux Lamiinae du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris [Coleoptera, Cerambycidae]. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, (New Series) 18 (1), 9 - 29." type="journal article" year="1982">Breuning (1982)</bibRefCitation>
described a 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D3EBFA72FEC9FA19" box="[151,277,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D3EBFA72FEC9FA19" box="[151,277,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species as member of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D166FA72FD4AFA19" baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[538,662,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D166FA72FD4AFA19" box="[538,662,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by comparison of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D009FA72FBF2FA19" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1970" box="[885,1070,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimonephelotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D009FA72FBF2FA19" box="[885,1070,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Mimonephelotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D729FA72FA40FA19" authority="(Breuning, 1970)" baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[1109,1436,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D729FA72FB0DFA19" box="[1109,1233,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B07FFA04401D79EFA72FA48FA19" author="Breuning, S. von" box="[1250,1428,1411,1437]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="363 - 377" refId="ref4097" refString="Breuning, S. von (1970) Nouveaux Coleopteres Cerambycidae Lamiinae des Collections du Museum de Paris (suite). Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris (2 eme serie) 42 (2), 363 - 377." type="journal article" year="1970">Breuning, 1970</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and then, he renamed it as 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D2AAFA56FC88FA45" authority="(Breuning, 1971)" baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[470,852,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimanhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D2AAFA56FD5FFA45" box="[470,643,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Mimanhammus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B07FFA04401D1E8FA56FC97FA45" author="Breuning, S. von" box="[660,843,1447,1473]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="77 - 78" refId="ref4141" refString="Breuning, S. von (1971) Quelques rectifications systematiques sur les Lamiaires (Col. Cerambycidae). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de Mulhouse, 1971, 77 - 78. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / bsef. 1972.21237" type="journal article" year="1971">Breuning, 1971</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The main differences are related to the body size (
<quantity id="4C849B13FFA04401D3E3FA3AFEC6FA61" box="[159,282,1483,1509]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.65" metricValueMax="4.4" metricValueMin="2.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" unit="mm" value="36.5" valueMax="44.0" valueMin="29.0">29–44 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D241FA3AFE65FA61" baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[317,441,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D241FA3AFE65FA61" box="[317,441,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 
<quantity id="4C849B13FFA04401D294FA3AFDBDFA61" box="[488,609,1483,1509]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" unit="mm" value="23.0" valueMax="27.0" valueMin="19.0">19–27 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D1F9FA3AFCDFFA61" authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[645,771,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D1F9FA3AFCDFFA61" box="[645,771,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the different elytral pattern (numerous small points of yellowish pubescence forming two more or less conspicuous spots in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D0D4FA1EFBF8F98D" baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[936,1060,1519,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D0D4FA1EFBF8F98D" box="[936,1060,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
versus an irregular ochreous pattern and a large pre-median whitish spot in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D101F9E2FD27F9A9" authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[637,763,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D101F9E2FD27F9A9" box="[637,763,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC336F6FFA04401D3BBF9C6FD16F939" blockId="2.[151,1437,1123,1725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">
The pronotal spines, long and acute in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D100F9C6FD24F9D5" baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[636,760,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D100F9C6FD24F9D5" box="[636,760,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, tend to disappear in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D097F9C6FBB5F9D5" authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[1003,1129,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D097F9C6FBB5F9D5" box="[1003,1129,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but they are still present in some Philippine species, though always shorter than those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D03CF9AAFC60F9F1" baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[832,956,1627,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D03CF9AAFC60F9F1" box="[832,956,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These differences suggest that 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D662F9AAFA40F9F1" authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[1310,1436,1627,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D662F9AAFA40F9F1" box="[1310,1436,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D12CF98EFD10F91D" baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[592,716,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D12CF98EFD10F91D" box="[592,716,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as 
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B07FFA04401D187F98EFC4AF91E" author="Gahan, C. J." box="[763,918,1663,1690]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="109 - 121" refId="ref4312" refString="Gahan, C. J. (1906) On a Collection of Longicorn Coleoptera from Selangor and Perak. Journal of the Federated Malay States Museum, 1, 109 - 121, pl. VI. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938809460949" type="journal article" year="1906">Gahan (1906)</bibRefCitation>
supposed; nonetheless, we prefer to conserve the current taxonomy waiting for further analyses.
</paragraph>
